U.S. Long-Term Sovereign Credit Rating Outlook Revised to Negative by S&P

-- B y   S t e v e n   F r o m m
-- 
2011-04-18T13:08:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-18/u-s-long-term-sovereign-credit-rating-outlook-revised-to-negative-by-s-p.html
Standard & Poor’s  Ratings Services
affirmed its AAA long-term and A-1+ short-term sovereign
credit ratings on the U.S. and revised its outlook on the long-
term rating to negative from stable.  Standard & Poor’s said that more than two years after the
beginning of the recent crisis, U.S. policymakers have not
agreed on a strategy to reverse recent fiscal deterioration or
address longer-term fiscal pressures.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steven Fromm at 
 sfromm@bloomberg.net  